    <mj-section padding="0px">
      <mj-column background-color="#00a8e1">
             <mj-text color="white" padding-left="40px" padding-top="0" padding-bottom="10px" font-family="Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif" font-size="14px" line-height="150%">
        <h3>What is Amazon’s Post A Truck? </h3>
        <ul padding-left="0px">
        <li>
      	Your company can post available empty capacity by specifying details such as when and where trucks are available, one-way/round-trip, and a minimum payout.   
        </li>
        <li>
   The Post A Truck page has new filtering capabilities that allow your company to set the maximum number of stops, exclude cities from your Post A Truck availability, and for One-Ways you can select multiple destination cities or regions (i.e., Northeast).
        </li>
        <li>
        If a Trip on Relay Load Board matches the availability your company posted and has a payout equal to or higher than the minimum payout that was entered, Amazon can automatically book the freight for your company. 
        </li>
        </ul>
    
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    
